A dramatization of the life of Macario Sakay, the last Filipino revolutionary to hold out against the Americans during the tumultuous period of the Filipino-American War which had supposedly ended March 23, 1901, with the capture of general Emilio Aguinaldo. A determined Sakay, however, led a guerilla group of ragtag armies in different parts of the country in the continued fight for independence before finally succombing to the vast number of resources of the American government.
